Installation step for angular
-Node js  -->download LTS not current from 
https://nodejs.org/en/download/
or
https://nodejs.org/en/blog/release/v12.13.0/
(after installation do restart)
-angular
-visual studio code -->https://code.visualstudio.com/download
(after installation do restart)

open CMD and Close other application if any open 
(e.g vscode, notepad etc)

Type
1.node --version
2.npm --version

To update node through npm
npm install npm@latest -g

To install TS
pc must be connected with an internet.
npm install -g typescript@4.1.3
Type 
tsc --version

To install angular
pc must be connected with an internet.
npm install -g @angular/cli@7.3.*

Type
3. ng --version

********************************************
if any error occur then use as below Command
npm cache clear --force
npm cache verify
********************************************

Directory
Folder Structure
Frontend
		-TypeScript
		-Angular 
1.open angular folder and after that open cmd

ng new hello-world
Note-(Here hello- world is project name) 
after hitting above command you will get below questions
Which you like to add angular routing? Yes or y 
and do hit enter key

Which stylesheet format would you like? 
do hit enerer key


2.after that do cd hello-world
3.and run the project
to run the project you need to hit this command
ng serve -o 
or
ng serve --open

after successful Creation its open browser automatically 
---> http://localhost:4200/



***if angular is already installed and want to take latest version
npm uninstall -g angular-cli
npm cache clean or npm cache verify #(if npm > 5)
npm install -g @angular/cli@7.3.*
















